Part2

Class UnitTest4

  • java.lang.Object
    • Part2.UnitTest4

  • public class UnitTest4
extends java.lang.Object
    Test4: Store a file on the local machine in a target TFS file specified by its path. Input: local file path, TFS file Functionality: If the TFS file exists then reutrn an error message. Otherwise, create the TFS file, read the conent of the local file and store it in the TFS File. Example: Test4 C:\MyDocuments\Image.png 1\File1.png If 1\File1.png exists then reutrn error. Otherwise, create 1/File1.png, read the content of C:\MyDocument\Image.png, write the retrieved content into 1\File1.png Unit4: Identical to Test4 from Part 1 with number of replicas as an additional input. Input: TFS file, local file path, Number of replicas Number of replicas must be a value greater than zero. Raise an error and do not create the file if the specified number of replicas is greater than the number of chunk servers.
